titlestmt.titleproper: Guide to the Brooklyn Historical Society Genealogical vertical files ARC.313
titlestmt.author: Kevina Tidwell and Maggie Schreiner

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2023-08-21 11:17:38 +0000.

did.unittitle: Brooklyn Historical Society Genealogical vertical files
did.abstract: This collection was compiled by Brooklyn Historical Society staff to organize their genealogical research and the research of other professional and amateur genealogists. The collection includes correspondence, newspaper clippings, notes, pedigree charts, and a limited number of photographs.
did.langmaterial: The majority of this collection is in English, with some materials in German, Dutch and French.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: This collection was compiled by Brooklyn Historical Society staff to organize their genealogical research and the research of other professional and amateur genealogists.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection includes compiled genealogical research, including correspondence, newspaper clippings, notes, pedigree charts, and a limited number of photographs. The files represent families from Long Island and the North East region of the United States, and also reflect on the institutional history of the Brooklyn Historical Society. Materials in the collections are both originals and reproductions.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research without restrictions.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: The copyright status of this collection has not been assessed. Please consult library staff for more details.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is arranged alphabetically by family name.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: This is an artificial collection, compiled by Brooklyn Historical Society staff at an unknown date.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Identification of item, date (if known); Brooklyn Historical Society Genealogical Vertical Files, ARC.313, Box and Folder number; Brooklyn Historical Society.
